children.text: Abstract: Since the last decade, graphics processing units (GPU) have dominated the world

children.block_description: A span of text inside a line.
children.text: of interactive computer graphics and visualization technology. Over the years,

children.block_description: A span of text inside a line.
children.text: sophisticated tools and programming interfaces (like OpenGL, DirectX API) greatly

children.block_description: A span of text inside a line.
children.text: facilitated the work of developers because these frameworks provide all fundamental

children.block_description: A span of text inside a line.
children.text: visualization algorithms. The research target is to develop a traditional CPU-based pure

children.block_description: A span of text inside a line.
children.text: software rasterizer. Although currently it has a lot of drawbacks compared with GPUs, the

children.block_description: A span of text inside a line.
children.text: modern multi-core systems and the diversity of the platforms may require such

children.block_description: A span of text inside a line.
children.text: implementations. In this paper, we are dealing with triangle rasterization, which is the

children.block_description: A span of text inside a line.
children.text: cornerstone of rendering process. New model optimization as well as the improvement and

children.block_description: A span of text inside a line.
children.text: combination of existing techniques have been presented, which dramatically improve

children.block_description: A span of text inside a line.
children.text: performance of the well-known half-space rasterization algorithm. The presented

children.block_description: A span of text inside a line.
children.text: techniques become applicable in areas such as graphics editors and even computer games.

children.block_description: A span of text inside a line.
children.text: Keywords: half-space rasterization; bisector algorithm; software rendering

children.text: Introduction

children.block_description: A span of text inside a line.
children.text: The history of computer visualization goes back several decades, but its

children.block_description: A span of text inside a line.
children.text: importance has grown more significantly in recent years. More advanced

children.block_description: A span of text inside a line.
children.text: graphical features are dominant almost everywhere these days, from traditional

children.block_description: A span of text inside a line.
children.text: desktop computers to mobile and embedded devices. This is a result of a long

children.block_description: A span of text inside a line.
children.text: development process, which was mainly induced by the appearance of graphical

children.block_description: A span of text inside a line.
children.text: processors. While in early computer visualization only slow CPUs were used to

children.block_description: A span of text inside a line.
children.text: perform every stage of the entire rasterization process, nowadays graphics cards

children.block_description: A span of text inside a line.
children.text: (target hardware) have taken over this role. The main development directions of

children.block_description: A span of text inside a line.
children.text: the area are inspired and usually controlled by the professional computer game

children.block_description: A span of text inside a line.
children.text: and media industry and the increasing demands for CAD/CAM systems.

children.text: However, we should not forget about the recent development of CPUs. Modern

children.block_description: A span of text inside a line.
children.text: CPUs have many advanced features due to multi-core technology and the

children.block_description: A span of text inside a line.
children.text: extended instruction set (e.g. SSE, AVX). Besides the development of the

children.block_description: A span of text inside a line.
children.text: instruction set and the increase of central cores, another important result is the

children.block_description: A span of text inside a line.
children.text: appearance of DDR4 type memories in 2014. Although these types are one order

children.block_description: A span of text inside a line.
children.text: of magnitude faster than older DDR3 RAMs, still cannot compete with the DDR5

children.block_description: A span of text inside a line.
children.text: type memory equipped in modern video cards. Nevertheless it is a significant step

children.block_description: A span of text inside a line.
children.text: forward to improve the speed of memory operations. The continuous development

children.block_description: A span of text inside a line.
children.text: of CPU technology encourages software developers to reconsider the structure and

children.block_description: A span of text inside a line.
children.text: logical model of their existing graphical applications. The usage of a multi-thread

children.block_description: A span of text inside a line.
children.text: game engine model is essential for today's AAA-type computer games.

children.block_description: A span of text inside a line.
children.text: Developers of the most advanced graphics engines (Unreal Engine, CryEngine,

children.block_description: A span of text inside a line.
children.text: Frostbite, etc.) have already recognized the potential of these new opportunities.

children.block_description: A span of text inside a line.
children.text: The question may arise, whether it makes sense to deal with CPU-based solutions

children.block_description: A span of text inside a line.
children.text: if powerful GPUs are available today. The answer has already been given by

children.block_description: A span of text inside a line.
children.text: leading video game developers. Some modern games apply the CPU to perform

children.block_description: A span of text inside a line.
children.text: specific tasks to reduce GPU load. Software occlusion culling - where the CPU is

children.block_description: A span of text inside a line.
children.text: used to render polygons to occlusion buffer rather than the GPU - is a good

children.block_description: A span of text inside a line.
children.text: example of this hybrid approach. Several well-known games (e.g. KillZone 3,

children.block_description: A span of text inside a line.
children.text: Battlefield 3, etc.) and game engines (e.g. CryEngine) apply similar technologies

children.block_description: A span of text inside a line.
children.text: because CPUs have no latency problem of occlusion queries. Rasterization is

children.block_description: A span of text inside a line.
children.text: usually done in small resolution (e.g. Battlefield uses

children.block_description: A span of text inside a line.
children.text: 256 \times 114

children.block_description: A span of text inside a line.
children.text: ) and occlusion

children.block_description: A span of text inside a line.
children.text: testing can be done using a hierarchical software z-buffer [12] [19].

children.block_description: A span of text inside a line.
children.text: Using all this as a starting point, the central question that motivates this paper is

children.block_description: A span of text inside a line.
children.text: how to improve one of the fundamental visualization algorithms, i.e. a polygon fill

children.block_description: A span of text inside a line.
children.text: based rasterization on CPUs. Our objective is to propose algorithms and

children.block_description: A span of text inside a line.
children.text: extensions for the half-space rasterization model, which can serve as the basis of a

children.block_description: A span of text inside a line.
children.text: graphics engine applying more complex, possibly a hybrid graphics pipeline using

children.block_description: A span of text inside a line.
children.text: CPU for specific tasks.

children.text: lighting, shadowing, volumetric lighting, fog, pixel accurate culling, etc.). These

children.block_description: A span of text inside a line.
children.text: engines were optimized for the Intel Pentium MMX processor family and their

children.block_description: A span of text inside a line.
children.text: rendering system was based on the scanline-based polygon filling approach

children.block_description: A span of text inside a line.
children.text: applying several additional technologies (e.g. BSP tree), so as to provide high

children.block_description: A span of text inside a line.
children.text: performance. After the continuous spreading of GPU-based rendering, software

children.block_description: A span of text inside a line.
children.text: rendering was pushed more and more into the background. Nevertheless, some

children.block_description: A span of text inside a line.
children.text: great results, e.g. Pixomatic Renderer developed by Rad Game Tools and the

children.block_description: A span of text inside a line.
children.text: Swiftshader [2] by TransGaming were achieved. Both products are fully DirectX 9

children.block_description: A span of text inside a line.
children.text: compatible, very complex and highly optimized taking advantage of multi-core

children.block_description: A span of text inside a line.
children.text: threading possibilities of modern CPUs. Their pixel pipeline can continuously

children.block_description: A span of text inside a line.
children.text: modify itself adapting to the actual rendering tasks. Since these products are all

children.block_description: A span of text inside a line.
children.text: proprietary, the details of their architectures are not available for the general

children.block_description: A span of text inside a line.
children.text: public. By developing DirectX, Microsoft provided the basis for the spread of

children.block_description: A span of text inside a line.
children.text: GPU technologies, and it also developed a software rasterizer called WARP [3].

children.block_description: A span of text inside a line.
children.text: The renderer is capable of taking advantage of multi-threads and in some cases it

children.block_description: A span of text inside a line.
children.text: is even able to outperform low-end integrated graphics cards.

children.block_description: A span of text inside a line.
children.text: In 2008, based on problem and demand investigations, Intel aimed to develop its

children.block_description: A span of text inside a line.
A span of text inside a line.
children.text: based video card within the Larrabee project [5]. In a technological sense, the

children.block_description: A span of text inside a line.
children.text: card was a hybrid of the multi-core CPUs and GPUs. Its purpose was to provide

children.block_description: A span of text inside a line.
children.text: x86 cores-based, fully programmable pipeline with 16-byte-wide SIMD vector

children.block_description: A span of text inside a line.
children.text: units. The new architecture made it possible for graphic calculations to be

children.block_description: A span of text inside a line.
children.text: programmed in a more flexible way than GPUs with an x86 instruction set.

children.block_description: A span of text inside a line.
children.text: Other researchers proposed optimization of the triangle traversal algorithms, and

children.block_description: A span of text inside a line.
children.text: new rasterization models have been introduced. As a part of current results,

children.block_description: A span of text inside a line.
children.text: Hengyong Jiangl et al. [13] proposed a midpoint triangle rasterization traversal

children.block_description: A span of text inside a line.
children.text: algorithm, which reduces the number of traversal points and improves the

children.block_description: A span of text inside a line.
children.text: efficiency of graphics acceleration. Their approach is demonstrated by an FPGA.

children.block_description: A span of text inside a line.
children.text: Pablo et al. investigated and compared three different triangle traversal algorithms

children.block_description: A span of text inside a line.
children.text: (Box, Zig-zag, Hilbert Curve based) in terms of performance and they simulated

children.block_description: A span of text inside a line.
children.text: them in Matlab using ModelSim [22]. Their experimental results show that

children.block_description: A span of text inside a line.
children.text: important area-performance trade-offs can be met, when implementing key image

children.block_description: A span of text inside a line.
children.text: processing algorithms in hardware. Chih-Hao Sun et al. [15] demonstrated an edge

children.block_description: A span of text inside a line.
children.text: equation based tile-scan triangle traversal algorithm. In their solution, the basic

children.block_description: A span of text inside a line.
children.text: functions of parameter interpolation and rasterization can be executed with a

children.block_description: A span of text inside a line.
children.text: universal shared hardware to reduce the cost of rendering. By hardware sharing

children.block_description: A span of text inside a line.
children.text: and architecture design techniques of pipelining and scheduling, their algorithm

children.block_description: A span of text inside a line.
children.text: can meet real-time requirements for graphics applications at reasonable hardware

children.block_description: A span of text inside a line.
children.text: costs. An entirely new approach was presented by Olano et al., which is a

children.block_description: A span of text inside a line.
children.text: simplified solution for triangle scan conversion applying 2D homogeneous

children.block_description: A span of text inside a line.
children.text: coordinates for fast real-time rendering [17]. Their solution avoids costly clipping

children.text: tests and can render true homogeneous triangles significantly faster than previous

children.text: Accelerated Half-Space Triangle Rasterization

children.block_description: A span of text inside a line.
children.text: using a block-based half-space theory where only the CPU is used for

children.block_description: A span of text inside a line.
children.text: calculations, which led to performance improvements [1]. The FreePipe Software

children.block_description: A span of text inside a line.
children.text: Rasterizer [9] focuses on multi-fragment effects, where each thread processes one

children.block_description: A span of text inside a line.
children.text: input triangle, determines its pixel coverage, and performs shading and blending

children.block_description: A span of text inside a line.
children.text: sequentially for each pixel. Due to the evolution of GPGPU, the idea of

children.block_description: A span of text inside a line.
children.text: performing software rendering by GPGPU has been raised several times. NVidia

children.block_description: A span of text inside a line.
children.text: proposed and investigated an efficient CUDA-based rendering model [6], the

children.block_description: A span of text inside a line.
children.text: performance of which is a factor of 2-8x compared to the hardware graphics

children.block_description: A span of text inside a line.
children.text: pipeline.

children.block_description: A span of text inside a line.
children.text: In recent years, major companies in the game industry have recognized the

children.block_description: A span of text inside a line.
children.text: potential of the CPU again [11]. Their game engine can delegate certain

children.block_description: A span of text inside a line.
children.text: visualization tasks to the CPU. In the game Battlefield 3 a SPU-based deferred

children.block_description: A span of text inside a line.
children.text: shading model was developed [12], where the objective was to use SPUs to

children.block_description: A span of text inside a line.
children.text: distribute shading work and offload GPU. In 2011, the game Killzone 3 supports

children.block_description: A span of text inside a line.
children.text: complex occluded environments. To cull non-visible geometry early in the frame,

children.block_description: A span of text inside a line.
children.text: the game uses PlayStation 3 SPUs to rasterize a conservative depth buffer and

children.block_description: A span of text inside a line.
children.text: performs fast synchronous occlusion queries against it

children.block_description: A span of text inside a line.
A span of text inside a line.
children.text: . The topic of software

children.block_description: A span of text inside a line.
children.text: occlusion culling has been investigated also by Intel Software in the paper [18]. It

children.block_description: A span of text inside a line.
children.text: presents a Killzone-like solution, but it is built upon an x86 basis and optimized

children.block_description: A span of text inside a line.
children.text: for SSE Streaming extensions.

children.block_description: A span of text inside a line.
children.text: Thus, as recent findings show, CPU-based approaches put an emphasis on again to

children.block_description: A span of text inside a line.
children.text: increase flexibility and performance. This paper investigates the optimization and

children.block_description: A span of text inside a line.
children.text: extensions of the triangle traversal and filling algorithm.

children.text: Basics of Rasterization

children.block_description: A span of text inside a line.
children.text: The aim of computer visualization is to display pixel sets (e.g. 2D image or

children.block_description: A span of text inside a line.
children.text: projected 3D objects) on the screen. The type of rendering algorithm or the

children.block_description: A span of text inside a line.
children.text: procedure of a presentable element largely depends on the applied hardware or

children.block_description: A span of text inside a line.
children.text: software based visualisation model. Rasterization is a very intensive process

children.block_description: A span of text inside a line.
children.text: computationally, especially when the visual element also contains an alpha

children.block_description: A span of text inside a line.
children.text: channel [7] [21].

children.block_description: A span of text inside a line.
children.text: Several approaches have been developed to represent shapes in memory, but

children.block_description: A span of text inside a line.
children.text: nowadays the most prevalent and most widely applied object representation is the

children.block_description: A span of text inside a line.
children.text: polygon mesh. During the modelling process the object is usually divided into

children.block_description: A span of text inside a line.
children.text: convex polygons, like triangles. Still, the rendering performance largely depends

children.block_description: A span of text inside a line.
children.text: on the applied rasterization algorithm. Although several different solutions have

children.block_description: A span of text inside a line.
children.text: been developed (Ray tracing, Volume Rendering, etc.), currently GPU

children.block_description: A span of text inside a line.
children.text: manufacturers use triangle filling based models in real-time visualisation. This

children.block_description: A span of text inside a line.
children.text: method allows significantly faster rendering than for example ray based

children.block_description: A span of text inside a line.
children.text: algorithms.

children.text: Triangle-based Filling

children.block_description: A span of text inside a line.
children.text: In a classical sense filling is performed pixel by pixel, so the inner iteration and

children.block_description: A span of text inside a line.
children.text: the various calculations need to be executed many times. Although the vertex

children.block_description: A span of text inside a line.
children.text: mapping and the traversal of the process seem to be simple, the filling

children.block_description: A span of text inside a line.
children.text: performance largely depends on the implemented algorithm and its optimization

children.block_description: A span of text inside a line.
children.text: level. We can state that it is a huge challenge to implement an algorithm, which

children.block_description: A span of text inside a line.
children.text: takes the possibilities of the modern CPU hardware into account and being highly

children.block_description: A span of text inside a line.
children.text: optimized at the same time. The parts of the filling model affect each other in a

children.block_description: A span of text inside a line.
children.text: complex form. The smallest change in the iteration logic can result in up to more

children.block_description: A span of text inside a line.
children.text: than a 10% performance difference.

children.block_description: A span of text inside a line.
children.text: Nowadays there are two widespread triangle filling algorithms: the scanline and

children.block_description: A span of text inside a line.
children.text: the half-space based algorithms. The main idea of the previous scanline approach

children.block_description: A span of text inside a line.
children.text: was to walk triangle line by line (scanline) from top to bottom. Each row

children.block_description: A span of text inside a line.
children.text: represents a line, whose starting and ending points are the intersections of the

children.block_description: A span of text inside a line.
children.text: triangle sides and the scanline along the

children.block_description: A span of text inside a line.
children.text: x

children.block_description: A span of text inside a line.
children.text: axis. The end points of the line can be

children.block_description: A span of text inside a line.
children.text: calculated incrementally using the slope values of the edges.

children.block_description: A span of text inside a line.
children.text: The scanline algorithm is widely used and can be optimized (e.g. s-buffer), but it

children.block_description: A span of text inside a line.
children.text: is difficult to adapt it to current hardware opportunities. The rasterization is

children.block_description: A span of text inside a line.
children.text: performed line by line, which has several unpleasant consequences for both

children.block_description: A span of text inside a line.
children.text: hardware and software implementation. One of these problems is that the

children.block_description: A span of text inside a line.
children.text: algorithm is asymmetric in

children.block_description: A span of text inside a line.
children.text: x

children.block_description: A span of text inside a line.
children.text: and

children.block_description: A span of text inside a line.
children.text: y

children.block_description: A span of text inside a line.
children.text: directions. In the case of thin triangles, the

children.block_description: A span of text inside a line.
children.text: performance may significantly vary between the horizontal and vertical

children.block_description: A span of text inside a line.
children.text: orientation. The outer scanline loop is serial, which is not favourable for hardware

children.block_description: A span of text inside a line.
children.text: implementation. The inner loop, which is responsible for scanline iteration is not

children.block_description: A span of text inside a line.
children.text: so SIMD-friendly because of the different line lengths. This makes the algorithm

children.block_description: A span of text inside a line.
children.text: orientation-dependent. Processing several lines at the same time for some reason

children.block_description: A span of text inside a line.
children.text: (e.g. Mipmapping, Multisampling) would mean further complications for

children.block_description: A span of text inside a line.
children.text: calculations. To sum up, the solution is hard to apply for parallel processing of

children.block_description: A span of text inside a line.
children.text: lines and pixels. A better solution would be if pixels were processed in 2x2 blocks

children.block_description: A span of text inside a line.
children.text: (quads), the expected increase in the performance would be significant.

children.block_description: A span of text inside a line.
children.text: Next, the paper focuses on the other approach, the half-space based triangle

children.block_description: A span of text inside a line.
children.text: traversal, where the basic algorithm and further optimization points are presented

children.block_description: A span of text inside a line.
children.text: which improves performance to a large extent.
